FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778796671
OL,3,CPolitical chaos is bad for the economy
OL,4,Cno matter who is in charge
OL,6,FWhoever is prime minister when the
OL,7,Fbloodshed stops faces a huge problem.
OL,9,FThe British economy grew strongly in
OL,10,Fthe first three months of the year but
OL,11,Fthat was also true in 2022, 2023, 2024
OL,12,Fand 2025.
OL,14,FIn each case, the wind dropped and we
OL,15,Fended up back in the doldrums.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778796671
OL,3,CPolitical chaos is bad for the economy
OL,4,Cno matter who is in charge
OL,6,FThe big challenge this time is that
OL,7,Fwar in the Gulf has caused a spike in
OL,8,Fthe price of gas and oil in particular
OL,9,F- and that's already pushing up prices
OL,10,Fand leaving businesses and households
OL,11,Ffeeling unsettled.
OL,13,FThe full impact of any disruption to
OL,14,Fthe Strait of Hormuz has yet to be
OL,15,Ffelt, but another cost of living
OL,16,Fsqueeze is coming.
OL,18,FThe Resolution Foundation estimates
OL,19,Fthat wages, adjusted for inflation,
OL,20,Fwill fall - leaving the average
OL,21,Fhousehold worse off.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778796671
OL,3,CPolitical chaos is bad for the economy
OL,4,Cno matter who is in charge
OL,6,FIt also says the government's finances
OL,7,Fcould be hit to the tune of #16
OL,8,Fbillion, restricting its ability to
OL,9,Fcushion the blow.
OL,11,FYou can't blame the government for the
OL,12,Fwar with Iran and its impact - pushing
OL,13,Fup petrol, diesel, energy bills and
OL,14,Ffood prices - but you can ask what the
OL,15,Fgovernment plans to do about it.
OL,17,FThe truth is the UK has been stuck in
OL,18,Fa low-growth rut for 16 years. Keir
OL,19,FStarmer was elected on a promise to
OL,20,Fget us out of it. He hasn't delivered
OL,21,Fyet.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778796671
OL,3,CPolitical chaos is bad for the economy
OL,4,Cno matter who is in charge
OL,6,FOn Monday, he promised to be bolder
OL,7,Fwithout offering a radical change of
OL,8,Fdirection.
OL,10,FIf he is deposed, an unpopular leader
OL,11,Fmay be removed but the underlying
OL,12,Feconomic problem remains. And it's not
OL,13,Fclear that his successors would have
OL,14,Fany better answers.
OL,16,FAmid the uncertainty, yields on UK
OL,17,Fgovernment bonds, a measure of the
OL,18,Fcost of government borrowing, have
OL,19,Frisen further.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
