OL,3,CPolitical chaos is bad for the economy
OL,4,Cno matter who is in charge
OL,6,F'Investors want to see is a government
OL,7,Fthat has clear plans to rein in
OL,8,Fborrowing' - Michael Saunders, Oxford
OL,9,FEconomics
OL,11,F"The UK has been a relatively weak
OL,12,Feconomic performer for a long time,
OL,13,Fbut now we've got a political mess on
OL,14,Ftop of that," says Michael Saunders of
OL,15,FOxford Economics, a former member of
OL,16,Fthe Monetary Policy Committee at the
OL,17,FBank of England.
OL,26,@sD@AOUvD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778796671
OL,3,CPolitical chaos is bad for the economy
OL,4,Cno matter who is in charge
OL,6,F"So I think what investors want to see
OL,7,Fis a government that has clear plans
OL,8,Fto rein in borrowing, revitalise the
OL,9,Feconomy, and improve its popularity so
OL,10,Fthat it is going to be here for the
OL,11,Flong run."
OL,13,FWhat are Wes Streeting's ambitions for
OL,14,Ftax, borrowing, spending, debt, public
OL,15,Finvestment, trade - and our
OL,16,Frelationship with the European Union?
OL,17,FWe don't really know.
OL,19,FWe do know that life with low economic
OL,20,Fgrowth is pretty miserable, and a very
OL,21,Fserious political problem.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@JO]
